					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Key=value could be used, and you also forgot some too including the keyboard, standard controller, player2 controller with SELECT/START, player2 controller with microphone, Super NES standard controller, different kind of 4-players adapters, and others.<br /><br />Other possible things to include in other section of such a file, might be NTSC/PAL/RGB/Dendy/multi (beyond the simple NTSC/PAL in the iNES ROM file), names of switches for Vs System, memory address labels, and so on.<br /><br />These information and others could be included in a separate file with the same name except extension, possibly INI which is not too complicated and that you can still add additional blocks if needed, and comments too (actually, possibly the file should have both extensions such as .NES.INI).<br /><br />Example:<div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">&#91;Main&#93;<br />Title=&quot;Famicom Hangman&quot;<br />TV=NTSC|RGB ; NTSC and RGB both work (emphasis bits are not used)<br />License=Unofficial ; Not officially license by Nintendo<br /><br />&#91;Controller&#93;<br />Players=1 ; Single player game<br />Expansion=Keyboard ; Using Famicom keyboard<br />Player2=|StandardMicrophone ; Player 2 controller is optional, and can use the microphone if available<br /><br />&#91;License&#93;<br />Name=&quot;Public domain&quot;<br />Watermark=No ; Copies are not watermarked<br />Copy=Allow<br />Modify=Allow<br />Commercial=Allow<br /><br />&#91;Mapper&#93;<br />Mirror=H|V|1|4 ; Program doesn't care about nametablem mirroring<br />RAM=0 ; PRG RAM is not used (this line is redundant if the ROM image is NES 2.0)<br />BusConflict=No|Yes ; Program doesn't care if bus conflicts are used or not<br /></div><br /><br />Sometimes a game might use multiple modes of what sets of input devices can be used:<div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">&#91;Controller&#93;<br />Modes=2<br />Player1=Standard ; Standard controller for player 1 always has SELECT/START buttons<br /><br />&#91;Mode0&#93;<br />Name=&quot;Single&quot;<br />Players=1<br /><br />&#91;Mode1&#93;<br />Name=&quot;Double&quot;<br />Players=2<br />Player2=Standard|StandardSelectStart ; Player 2 can use SELECT/START buttons if it has them, but is not required<br /></div></div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="gopher://zzo38computer.org/" class="postlink">.</a></div>
