				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The main game cartridge format ought to describe what's on the PCB in enough detail that a functionally equivalent reproduction can be built. (The one exception to this that I can think of is an ADPCM playback chip in a few Famicom games such as Moero Pro Yakyuu.) Labels, boxes, instructions, and controller configuration can be handled with a separate file, just as the cartridge case, box, instruction manual, and controllers are separate physical things.<br /><br />What's so special about iNES is that the vast majority of dumps floating around are in this format, and it's still dead easy to parse even on an 8-bit machine.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

